---
title: Creamy Garlic Chicken Spaghetti with Nutmeg, Parmesan & Chives
description: This is our platonic ideal of a pasta meal—dreamy bowls of velvety spaghetti. You’ll simmer up a rich, creamy sauce tinged with a pinch of nutmeg for a subtle hint of warming spice (trust us, it’s the secret ingredient!), then add in al dente pasta and finish with juicy, garlicky seared chicken and a flourish of chopped chives and crushed red chili flakes. Work up that appetite, cause you’re in for a perfect bowl of luxurious pasta ready to be lovingly twirled and devoured.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/661d66433d20ae432f30b550-b4321f52.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/661d66433d20ae432f30b550-en-US.pdf
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 47 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 500 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-garlic-chicken-spaghetti-661d66433d20ae432f30b550
time required: 25 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Southern Europe
---

Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While spaghetti cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}.
Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1⁄2 inch thick.
Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}.
Wipe out pan; let cool slightly.

Once spaghetti is drained, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken
over medium-low heat. Add minced garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon},
1⁄4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and
@nutmeg{1%teaspoon}.

> Be sure to measure nutmeg—we sent more! If sauce is too thick, stir in
> more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.

Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low and cook, stirring constantly,
until warmed through.

Add drained spaghetti to pan and toss until thoroughly coated. Remove from heat.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide spaghetti between shallow #bowls{}. Top with chicken, chives,
and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.